# Atlas environment configuration — copy to `.env` and fill in.
# `.env` is gitignored; this template is committed.
#
# PostHog telemetry keys. These are read by `scripts/with-posthog-env.mjs`,
# which loads this file and exports the values before the Rust compile so they
# are baked into the binary at build time via `option_env!`
# (see src-tauri/src/telemetry/mod.rs). They are ALSO honored at runtime
# (loaded via dotenvy) for `cargo run` / source dev without the wrapper.
#
# A PostHog *project* key is a write-only ingest key — safe to ship in a client
# app. Leave blank to build Atlas with telemetry permanently inert.

# Project API key, e.g. phc_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
ATLAS_POSTHOG_KEY=

# Ingest host. Defaults to PostHog US cloud when blank.
# US: https://us.i.posthog.com   EU: https://eu.i.posthog.com
ATLAS_POSTHOG_HOST=https://us.i.posthog.com
